Apply Now        Request Information        Events                                                              All courses in the M.S. in Integrated Marketing program are marketing focused. Students begin with a set of core courses. They then select from three concentration areas: digital marketing, brand management, or marketing analytics. To complete the degree, students take the capstone course.   The curriculum consists of 14 courses. Each course is three credits, for a total of 42 credits. All courses are offered in the evenings to accommodate the needs of working professionals and to allow full-time students to participate in internships.   Full-time students complete the degree in two years, part-time students may take up to five years to complete the course of study, depending upon the number of courses they take each semester. Apply Now        Request Information        Events                                                              All courses in the M.S. in Integrated Marketing program are marketing focused. Students begin with a set of core courses. They then select from three concentration areas: digital marketing, brand management, or marketing analytics. To complete the degree, students take the capstone course.   The curriculum consists of 14 courses. Each course is three credits, for a total of 42 credits. All courses are offered in the evenings to accommodate the needs of working professionals and to allow full-time students to participate in internships.   Full-time students complete the degree in two years, part-time students may take up to five years to complete the course of study, depending upon the number of courses they take each semester.
